inn1.comm: pushed to short midwicket first up
nudged down off the back foot into the leg side and Hayden's off the mark
defended on the front foot first up
moves back into the line of the ball, on off, and pushed down off the back foot
off the mark with a shuffle into the leg side
a hint of swing in the air, but Hayden doesn't miss out on the chance to drive strongly through mid-off
room on on the off side, Clarke cuts strongly off the back foot
tighter delivery, defended on the front foot
more defence again
pushed towards short midwicket this time
outside off, played well through gap in front of midwicket, Clarke picking the gap really well
defended on the front foot
flashed away at that one off the back foot, connecting only with air
defended on the front foot
down the track and Hayden pulls strongly on the front foot through midwicket, but it's well tidied up inside the boundary by Hopkins, scooping it back in
straight down, nudged into short midwicket, and Hayden sends Clarke back very quickly indeed
comes forward to defend on the front foot
outside off, Clarke nearly drags an inside edge on, he didn't know too much about it, but ends up stepping on the ball
pushed off the back foot through midwicket
Clarke falls early, Gillespie gets him with a well-directed short ball which Clarke tries to pull and instead skies an edge short in on the off side
pushed off the back foot into midwicket
defended on the back foot towards short mid-off
defended this time
low full toss, Hayden simply launches into that with a full cover drive that powers away to the rope
nipped back, hit him in a painful place, Ponting mouthing "Ooh", as do others with the replay
down the channel, shoulders arms as this rushes through outside off
beats him all ends up down off, Ponting playing outside it, the ball just failing to take his inside edge
the ball spits up this time, Ponting fending down, one-handed, in to the leg side
in the air, but very safe, Hayden squirting square for a one-bounce four. That was travelling
pushed forward, no run this time
pushed forward for a quick single
turns it to leg, not the most convincing shot ever, and indeed it is a leg bye
outside off, plenty of room, shouts of "Catch" as Ponting places that up and over the covers
outside off, laced through cover off the back foot
movement outside off, left alone this time
on leg, picked up well off the legs, a Pietersen-esque flamingo flung in to boot, and away it runs through midwicket
driven straight to the man at mid off
played down straight off the back foot
driven right back to the bowler who shapes aggressively to try to run out Hayden, who was coming down the crease, forcing him back to his mark
pushed across the left hander who drives to mid off this time
strayed down leg, Hayden turns it behind square, where there's some excellent relaying back in
finds the gap short in square and an easy single results
slowish ball to start, outside off, pushed into short midwicket
down the track, pulled with control to midwicket
played straight back down off the back foot
wide this time, just a misdirection down leg
defended strongly into the short cover region
defensive push into the covers, shaping to attack
nipped back in to the right hander, who catches it between his calves, that's not a bad take at all, and begins hopping around before picking it out and returning to New Zealand
slower ball, half-volley, Hayden has all the time in the world, waiting and driving on one knee through the covers
turns round square to try to pull it
defended on the front foot
pushed off the back foot
nipped back in off the seam from outside off, good delivery, Ponting cramped for room as he tried to cut
outside off, driven straight to the man short in on the off
pushed back straight
angles in at the left hander from round the wicket, tightening him up, Hayden playing forward without much power
pushed off the legs to midwicket
just up there, Hayden pushes towards Oram who does well to make a tidy stop
in at the left hander again, who defends
tight in again at the left hander to round off a decent maiden
pushed off the front foot to leg
outside off, driven to mid off
on middle, pushed out to square where Taylor returns well
on leg, turned out just behind square where Gillespie is the fielder this time
outside off, cut to point
up there, straight, Ponting rocks back and peels off a cut to point
short, and pulled in front of midwicket
down the wicket to a short one, there's a top-edge pull and now Hayden's gone
pushed forward to the covers
on off, popped up a touch, Ponting pushed it towards mid on this time
change of pace, a touch outside off, Ponting creams a cut to the covers
nipped in from outside off, driven forward back to the bowler
starts tidily, on middle and leg, defended forward
driven straight to the man at cover
outside off, cut out to point
big loop, on leg, driven out to a wideish mid-on where again there's some decent fielding
pushed to cover for an easy single
spins in from round the wicket, Ponting pushing back out in front of midwicket
a rare miss of a pull shot for Ponting
defended forward
tucked right in to the right hander who defends into the covers
turned round the corner this time
driven out to short cover
outside off, watches it go past his edge
driven into the covers
turned towards square leg
defended on the front foot this time
reaches out to turn off the legs through midwicket
reaches out to pull down towards fine
played square of the wicket, towards cover point
nipped back in from outside off, a slower ball this time
defended forward with a touch of defence
right up there, defended again, this time on the back foot
popped up this time in front of midwicket, agonisingly in front of Styris and they get a run on the misfield
driven into short cover this time
opened the face, but guided it straight towards short third man, and Australia continue to be tucked up
pushed in short on the off side
quick single to mid-on
down the pitch, in the air, just wide of Patel's outstretched hand at midwicket
a controlled single forward
what looked like an edge back towards the gully, bouncing jus tin front
on a leg line, Hussey drives straight to the man at midwicket, then rehearses his shot
dragged down, pulled in front of short midwicket
opens the face, guides well down through gully with good control
Ponting helps a well-timed pull up and behind square for a one-bounce four
wide outside off, driven to the covers this time but picks out the fielder, good work from the fielder
steps down the track and drives in front of midwicket
pushed off the back foot towards short third man, a single there as Mills can't stop it
cut off the back foot outside off
up there, defended into the off side off the back foot
short and Hussey lifts over midwicket where Taylor gives chase in vain
defended into the leg side
driven out towards mid-on, a tight run there, but in as Hopkins' throw from mid-on misses the stumps
outside off, lifted up and over mid-off for an easy boundary
a much-deserved wicket for Oram, Hussey lofting the ball straight to extra cover where How takes a straightforward catch. So Australia struggling a touch now, having set off on a decent note
tidy defence on the back foot this time
defended once more, the ball nipping right in
a mirror image of the previous ball
flashing cut up and over the slips, he'd reckon that was deliberate, but it was a top edge clearing gully, Mills tidying up inside the rope
defended on the back foot
pushed off the toes through fine where Sinclair does the job
on leg, pushed out past mid-on, a lovely play off the pads and they settle for two
tidy defence on the front foot, though there's a very hopeful shout, and turned down
comes out to defend on the front foot once more
right up there, Symonds forced to defend once more
right up there, pushed into the covers for a quick single
defended on the back foot this time
turned off the legs to midwicket for a single, giving the strike back to Ponting
on middle and leg, defended into short midwicket, no chance of a run
dragged short and pulled in front of midwicket
paddled down off the back foot, tucked into the leg-side, where Styris does the fielding
slower delivery, worked out towards midwicket for another single, this one a strike-stealing number
worked to the covers to bring up the hundred
the strike's rotated once again into the covers this time
defended on the back foot this time
short ball, Symonds defended into the off side, that surprised him with the lift and ever so nearly tucked back on to his stumps, the ever-alert Ponting calls him through
not quite timed back to the bowler
shot of the day brings up a well-deserved fifty, drilled through cover
Symonds drives to a very deep long-off
on middle stump, turned to the legs
drives safely to long-off for an easy run
outside off, lashed off the back foot forward of point
How tidies up at short midwicket
Symonds with a slightly lofted shot forward, but finds space easily enough
pushed off the back foot
outside off, Ponting shapes to drive into the covers
outside off, driven strongly off the back foot to point
outside off, nipping back in straight, Ponting leans in to try to force it past point but in comes Patel
great shot, a lofted drive right over long-on that races away
good reply, a dot, driven out to mid-on
a mix up there between Ponting and Symonds, who both set off, it could have been close if Patel had returned more cleanly from third man
cuts back to Patel this time
drives towards point where Patel does the job
pushed into the covers
down the track and there's another clean hit, Ponting picking it up with the base of the bat and elevating a drive wide of long-on
defended on the front foot
defended on the back foot
outside off, Symonds stands tall and cuts over point, a strong, deliberate shot and the crowd love it
short of a length, a classic back-foot drive this time, top timing and placement
outside off and Symonds drives again on the up through cover
pushed back but no run this time
down leg, tucked off the toes through midwicket, another decent shot but only for two
width outside off, chopped away through point
moved out through to deep cover this time
cover drive now
a back-foot drive but can't find its way past Taylor
on one knee, swept well, with good control, behind square
outside off, dragged a touch low, Symonds fails to cut fully, Vettori gets away with it
reaches out to defend into the covers
down the track, Symonds comes down the track to defend this time
down the track and whipped over mid-on, landing safe in front of long-on, Symonds taking that one from outside off
on middle and leg and brisked through midwicket
Symonds dances down and punches to midwicket but can't pierce the field in the form of Taylor
outside off this time, Patel round the wicket, Symonds pushes into the covers
round the wicket, Ponting leans in to a push to the covers, no single on there
a touch short, Ponting pulls in front of leg for a good save just inside the line
up there, defended on the front foot
on off, cut away off the back foot through point
comes down on one knee, shovelled round to fine leg
cut away through backward point
turned off the legs through fine
a quick single
more strike rotation
Ponting drills that hard down the ground
a huge six to bring up the 150, using his feet and a big swish over the midwicket area
round the wicket, darted in, pushed off the pads
pushed to the covers for a quick single
on leg, glanced fine through fine leg
pushed into the legs
drives down the ground
more milking continues
outside leg, tucked back down there to fine
down the track, Symonds smashes towards mid-off, a touch aerial
outside off, cuts just under the ball, the bails coming off as McCullum grabbed the ball and tried for the stumping
pushed away from the body outside off, beaten outside the off stump
up there, defended on the back foot
pushed off the front foot to midwicket
a dab to short third man, no chance for a run
plays on the on side towards short midwicket
swings across the line, beating short midwicket, and it's tidied up just outside the circle
driven out to long on
driven out to long on, again
Symonds defends back to the bowler this time
poked off the legs for a quick single
dancing down, rolls out forward of square
pulled away through midwicket
down leg, Symonds plays off the back foot behind square
Ponting gets right into the crease and rotates the strike again with a push to Vettori
defended straight on the back foot
Ponting drives to cover
on the back foot this time
tucked off the back foot through to third man
turned off the legs in front of midwicket
oh, massive loft on the on-side, nearly clears the ropes
pitched up and driven along the ground
worked out on the off side
short of a length outside off, drives out there to take him to 90
wide down leg
wide outside off, cut inside the rope, Mills with the return throw
outside leg, worked off the toes round to fine
pushed into the off
Ponting lofts right over midwicket
drives to long off, the first one taken quickly, but there's no chance for a second
another quick single to rotate the strike again
worked off the legs and they come back for two
whipped behind square this time
defended forward, no chance for a single
outside off, tried to squeeze down on the back foot, with not much room but he gets the single and the strike again
straight drive to bring up back-to-back centuries following on from Adelaide (he obviously didn't bat in Sydney)
Ponting hooks in the deep this time
cut away off the back foot, beating gully and that rolls on to bring up his half century
but falls the next ball. That's a huge wicket for New Zealand, Symonds falling across the line and trapped in front, low
shouldered arms first up
another dot
steered off the front foot
that one kept low, unusually for today, Haddin poking down on the back foot in the end
pushed into the covers and off the mark at last, Ponting back on strike
waits and leg-glances behind square leg
strikes down the wicket straight back to Vettori
a bit of air, flicks into leg
a dot first up
late cut down to third man
rocked back for a crunching low hook through midwicket
good, aggressive running out to midwicket
outside off, cut hard to point, with a risky-ish single
down the track, drives hard forward, but Mills picks it up on the follow-through
Ponting tries to force it on the off side
Ponting drives to cover
a bit of air, defended on the back foot
pushed off the back foot short in on the off side
more loop, defended on the front foot
turned to the legs
on middle, Ponting plays to the on side for a very quick single
down the track and Haddin turns it into a good length ball, forcing it into the off side
drove out to long on, two more runs for Australia
outside off, clever ball, beating Haddin who doesn't connect as he tries to work it down to third man
down the track, lofted high and in front of midwicket
huge strike over midwicket, lofted high and higher, clean striking at its best
good length, straight, Ponting tries to pull it behind square but hardly timed it at all
down the track and Haddin launches that through the on-side, good use of the bottom hand
right up there, but digs it out to long on for a single, bringing Ponting back on strike
driven out to mid-on for another comfortable one
low full toss, driven out to deep cover
outside off, driven out to deep cover, slightly uppishly
up there, on middle and off, driven out to mid-on
down the track and tickles that behind him and they come back for a decent two
pushed forward
full toss, got away with it, Ponting chipping over the infield just inside the rope
down the track, nearly yorks himself, digs it out to long on for a single in the end
a touch short, driven out in front of midwicket
driven on the up to extra cover
comes across the sticks, trying to drive off into the on side, but misses out on that one
full toss just came out wrong, Ponting lashes hard through long-off, but Oram gets away with it this time
outside off, a slower ball just short of a length, Haddin cuts and doesn't get back into his ground, Hopkins tidying up from backward point, and McCullum taking the return shy
down leg, Hopes off the mark immediately, Gillespie just behind square getting a hand on it
a dot finishes off a fine spell from Oram, 10-1-34-2
drives him down the ground for a comfortable single
outside off, cut into the ground off the bottom of the bat
outside off, pulled just in front of Taylor at midwicket
low full toss, Ponting drives out to long off
on leg, tucked into the midwicket region
right up into the blockhole, driven out to mid on, and they get two with the return
launched in front of midwicket, Hopes is just safe as Mills chased it back
smashed back to Gillespie and that raps him hard on the left foot
launches a drive to long off
round the wicket, a bump ball edge into the ground off a cover drive, taken cleanly by McCullum, with a low dive to his right
in he comes again, driven in the air on the bounce
outside off, launches an edge wide of McCullum for four
Mills bowls, dug out to midwicket, the throw deflects off the stumps and they think about taking a third
tucked into short midwicket and Australia think about a second, which was never on, but they're keeping up the pressure
low full toss driven out to mid-on
follows the batsman as he backs off towards leg, driven out to mid off
driven on the up out towards long-on, bouncing once before Patel picks it up cleanly
follows the batsman wide of leg agian, good bowling, worked behind point
outside off, blazed wide of cover, one hand coming off the bat
down leg, tripped off the toes to fine
right up there, driven straight out to long-on
full toss driven up and over the infield in front of midwicket, great swing
wide outside off, driven to cover where there's a tidy return to Gillespie who breaks the stumps and Hopes is well out, no need for a replay, he wasn't even in the frame
driven out in front of midwicket and Australia end with 6 for 282

inn2.comm: left alone outside off first up
straight, pitching on middle and leg, a dink and shuffle through
pushed down into the off side
hurried through, good carry, the batsman attempts the pull from outside off (obviously not learning from Clarke's dismissal earlier) and Lee appeals for a non-existent under edge
pace again, the ball scurrying through scurrilously, just too good for the batsman
tight and up there
pushed through down the channel, the in-form McCullum leaves that one alone
wild, yet safe, edge wide of the gully
bent away outside off
pushed forward this time
nipped across the right hander, who defends stoutly into the covers
straight, and pushed into short midwicket
pushed past his eyebrows, McCullum swaying back
stands tall and eases into the covers
up and over Haddin's outstretched hand, an upper cut
tries the same shot, gets a hard flash instead
McCullum goes early, a big wicket for Australia, and he will kick himself for that shot, flapping at a wide, slower, swinging ball, Haddin taking the faint edge through tidily
a sharp bouncer greets him
defended this time
more defence
driven on the up back towards the bowler
driven to mid-on, a quick single
played into the off side
swing away from the right hander, who shapes to cut
yorker, pushed up there, defended forward
a second catch for Braddin, a nick off the toe of the bat, and Sinclair, trying to cut off the back foot, is snapped wide with a tumble to his right
played down defensively off the back foot, jumping in the effort
pushed down off the back foot into the on side
wide outside off, driven straight to cover
too sharp for McCullum, the ball just outside off and nipping out, Styris manages to get some bat on it and pokes it down wide of third man
short ball, Styris deals with it
threatening wavy swing, punched down off the back foot
moved across the right hander from over the wicket, who opts to leave
outside off, finds the man at cover
drives straight back to the bowler
driven out through the covers on the up and that takes New Zealand to double figures. They've got to start somewhere
pushed down off the back foot, opening the face to guide it wide of third man
defended on the back foot
defended on the front foot, though not convincingly, an inside edge squirting towards the sticks
tries to drive on the up, and indeed does so, but picks out the fielder at cover
straight bouncer, periscopically ducked under
nipped in from just outside off, a good eye from the batsman, firstly connecting well and then picking the gap wide of cover, although it's then hunted down inside the rope
driven to the covers
pushed into the leg side
pushed through to the keeper
slower delivery, plenty of bend on it, not quite a banana more a (insert less bendy fruit here)
pushed across the right hander who eases it through the covers. Neat bit of timing
outside off, just driven into the on side
driven out to mid off, Hogg throws and misses the sticks, Hussey back up
on middle and leg, pushed back down into the leg side
sharp again from Lee, turned away into the leg side
drove away an outside edge behind point, was aiming through the covers, one hand coming up off the bat
outside off, inside edge driven out, unintentionally, into the leg side
straight bouncer, more periscoping
outside off, driven wide through the covers
outside off, pushed down through third man
pushed into the covers for a quick single
up there, waited, pushed into the covers again
driven through the covers
pushed off the back foot through to third man
chopped away behind point, so a more productive over which will encourage New Zealand at the end of the tenth over
pushed off the legs through fine
nipped in from outside off, defended straight back down
wide, cut wider
tried to pull that from outside off into the leg side
pushed up there, defended on the front foot
short ball, pulled through midwicket, ruining Tait's chance of a maiden (to take to Tasmania)
cuts back in from outside off and he strikes immediately! A big beam for Hopes, as there was no foot movement from the batsman
pushes forward and gets it right in the middle of the bat with the defence
looks to take that from outside off and drive through mid-on, but checks the shot
pushes on the rise into the covers
pushed towards the gully on the up
turned square off the legs
ah hello, Tait too good, beating the outside edge of the bat here
on middle and leg, turned through square, Australia looking ominous right now
swung in from just outside off, pushed to mid-on defensively
inside edged out in front of midwicket, Hussey tidies up and then shouts something encouraging
up there, stands tall, drives out to cover
pushed in from outside off, a direct hit from Clarke from point but he was well in
worked behind square leg for a single
squares up to it, pushed into the covers
pushed out to point, there's no run there
driven into the covers
flayed away, great shot
slashes outside off stump, gets the edge down to third man
played out through point
a big swish outside off stump, down on one knee, nearly got the under edge
right up there, finds the gap between mid on and midwicket, right out there
down the leg side, leg byes signalled
a swing and a miss, trying to hit through the line, but the ball was too quick and nipped back in trapping him in front of his stumps
single first ball, Lee has a shy at the stumps, but misses
outside off, whipped through to the gloves of Haddin, nipping away from the left hander
pushed across him once more
opens the face and runs it down to deep third man
down leg, tidied by the man short in at fine leg, quickly whizzed back
cut down to third man for a quick single
beaten him again
outside off, crashing square cut off the middle which races away
straight delivery, defended
down leg, a one-day wide, that'n, would've got away with it in Tests
on middle, driven out to mid on
stands tall, drives on the up straight back to the bowler
outside off, hammered through the covers, hit on the rise
driven into the covers
driven out towards cover point where Hayden tidies it
played just behind square, fielded by Clarke
the dangerman goes, Oram sending that up and up towards backward square leg where Lee comes in off the rope to take a very good catch, low
worked out to the off-side
played through the on side this time and gets a boundary second ball
shoulders arms to that one
swing in to the right hander, who drives to cover
pushed back to the bowler
nipped in to the right hander who pushes it back out to cover
swing in again, on the money, defended forward
whipped off the legs to midwicket
pushed up there, defended on the front foot
pushed into the covers, and Ponting cuts off any chance of a run
pushed into the covers
a nibble and run
Hopkins defends forward on the off side
short of a length, played on the rise into the covers
run off the back foot behind gully
down leg, pushed off the hips behind square
pushed into the off side
ooh, hit him on the toe then the bat, a huge appeal, and would have gone on to hit middle stump but he's got the benefit of the doubt
pushed to a wideish mid-on, great timing by Styris
beaten outside off stump, the ball nipping back in and just failing to take the edge
outside off, clean strike through the covers
pushed into the covers
inside edge back towards the sticks
turned behind square for an easy two
on middle, turned away behind square this time
pushed off the back foot, forced into the covers
defended on the rise, through the line to extra cover
pushed down off the back foot for a tip and run
slower ball, near off stick, played into the covers
pushed off the back foot to Clarke in the covers
pushed right up there, defended into the leg side
defended this time
Styris played on the up to the covers
pushed back in to the right hander, who defends
tight again, poked forward
and the change has worked, Hopkins flicking up off his legs, Clarke making yards with his dive to take a good, low catch at short backward square
defended forward
left alone as that turned outside off
and he's gone. Two wickets in the over for Hogg, a very sorry Vettori walks off after edging through one which was leaving him, so it's another catch for Haddin
short, cannons straight in to him as he tries to swivel pull to square
defended forward towards mid-on
drives on the up towards the covers
overstepped there
driven right over the top, great shot from Mills, over point for four
driven into the leg side this time
waits and drives into the covers
defended first up
a strike-rotating single
another dot, they are going to have do better than this
played off the legs
launches into that one on off
wide down leg
pushed forward
off the pads
pushed into the off side
outside off, played down to the gully
strong down the off side
strayed down leg
and again
amusing bouncer, pretty slow (comparatively)
played off the legs in front of square
in the air, sweeping, Hussey thought of a catch for a second
turned off the legs, square
huge shot up and over, right out of the screws as they say
defended
another smash in front of midwicket
yorker cleans him up, not much Mills could have done about that
pushed behind, tried to run down the off channel  inswinging
short ball, ducked under
ran wide down leg
pushed back to third man
defended on the back foot
played out to point
forward comes Gillespie, defending
pushed down to third man
defended on the front foot
turned off the legs behind square
over extra cover, Bracken dived just inside the rope
driven off the back foot to the covers
sharp bouncer
more of the short stuff, the crowd love this of course
pushed right up there, stabbed back forward defensively
up there on leg, raps him on the leg in front of leg
good aerial swing, overpitched a touch, pushed to the covers straight to Symonds who shies down one stick
pushed on to the leg, defended to that side
wrong'un, turned across the right hander who left it at the last second
backed away to cut, leaving his stumps exposed
up and over, slogged six by Gillespie, down on one knee and smote cleanly
swept square past Ponting
backs away, leaving the stumps open, but connects well to the off side and it's tidied with a slide in the deep
lofted down the ground, a straight hit and a two-bounce four
driven square through the off side, another clean strike just behind point
flat six across the line, oh hang on, was it, that hit the rope. The video umpire is getting a call. Ah, he's signalled four
bouncer on leg, pulled through midwicket
full yorker from the top drawer, Styris backs away and his middle stump is shattered
pushed right up there, Patel defends
turned back in to him, defended on the back foot and they grab a single
has a swing, lobbed away towards wideish long-on, and he's off the mark
driven over cover
straight drive back down the ground
straight delivery, Gillespie backs away, exposing the sticks, but misses the cut and the ball bounces over
drags short and swung to Symonds at midwicket and that's all over
